name: language_html_data_script_backtick
description: |
  Backtick terminates a JavaScript template literal. Code that safely handles
  single- and double-quoted strings can still break when a template literal is
  introduced during refactoring.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
pair:
  - with: template-expression.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "language"
  - "html"
  - "xss"
  - "xss-data"
  - "script-context"
  - "template-literal"
  - "backtick"
  - "contextual-escaping"
---
`
